c="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Stephen Stills, Democratic presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr. and Eric Clapton" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stills-Kennedy-Clapton@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eric-clapton">Eric Clapton</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stephen-stills">Stephen Stills</a> have helped raise millions of dollars for the Presidential campaign of controversial Democratic candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-features/ultimate-band-line-up-supergroups-3451774">What&#39;s your ultimate band line-up? NME writers pitch their dream supergroup</a></strong></li></ul><p> Kennedy Jr. is a member of the most famous political family in the US and has begun his Presidential campaign after spending three years as an environmental activist.</p><p> He is running against current US President <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/joe-biden">Joe Biden</a> and is a fringe candidate in the Democratic Party. However, following on from his environmental work, he has quickly become a figure of controversy due to his strong stance against vaccines.</p><p> Now, at a private fundraising event in Brentwood earlier this week, rock icons Eric Clapton and Stephen Stills helped Kennedy raise millions for his campaign.</p><p> According to a report by <a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/eric-clapton-robert-f-kennedy-jr-fundraiser-california-1235594599/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Hollywood Reporter</em></a> , Clapton performed with his band at the fundraiser and helped raise a total amount of $2.3million (£1.85million).</p><p> Of this amount, $1million (£805,000) went to benefit Kennedy&#39;s campaign, while the remaining $1.3million (£1.05million) went to a political action committee (PAC), which supports Kennedy Jr.&#39;s candidacy.</p><p> Other famous faces in attendance included Kennedy&#39;s wife and <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/curb-your-enthusiasm"><em>Curb Your Enthusiasm</em></a> star Cheryl Hines, Alicia Silverstone, actor and comedian Rob Schneider, and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/crosby-stills-nash-and-young">Crosby, Stills, Nash &amp; Young</a> musician, Stills. </p><figure id="attachment_3501826" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3501826" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3501826" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Stephen Stills performs at the Autism Speaks Light Up The Blues 6 Concert at The Greek Theatre on April 22, 2023" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Stephen-Stills@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3501826" class="wp-caption-text"> Stephen Stills performs at the Autism Speaks Light Up The Blues 6 Concert at The Greek Theatre on April 22, 2023. CREDIT: Harmony Gerber/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> It remains unclear whether or not the latter also performed at the fundraiser last week, however, his attendance was confirmed by recently circulated photos of himself, Clapton, and Kennedy standing together.</p><p> “I am deeply grateful to Eric Clapton for bringing his musical artistry and rebellious spirit to my gathering in Los Angeles last night,” Kennedy said in a statement (via <em>THR</em> ).</p><p> “I sometimes think that in our divided society, it is music rather than any kind of intellectual agreement that has the most potential to bring us together again. Eric sings from the depths of the human condition,” he added.</p><p> “If he sees in me the possibility of bringing unity to our country, it is only possible because artists like him invoke a buried faith in the limitless power of human beings to overcome any obstacle.”</p><p> The support from Clapton follows the guitarist also establishing himself as an opponent of the <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/coronavirus">COVID</a> vaccine ever since it was developed. </p><figure id="attachment_3501822" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3501822" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3501822" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Eric Clapton." width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Eric-Clapton@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3501822" class="wp-caption-text"> Eric Clapton. CREDIT: Mike Marsland/WireImage/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> In 2021 the artist revealed that he would <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/eric-clapton-says-he-will-not-play-venues-that-require-proof-of-vaccination-2999846">refuse to perform at any venue that required proof of vaccination</a> . He later <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/eric-clapton-announces-new-anti-lockdown-song-with-van-morrison-2826978">joined Van Morrison on an anti-lockdown song</a> .</p><p> Stills hasn&#39;t shared his political stance on vaccinations like Kennedy and Clapton, however he did <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/graham-nash-pulls-music-from-spotify-i-completely-agree-with-my-friend-neil-3151288">join the rest of his Crosby, Stills and Nash bandmates in removing their music from Spotify last year</a> .</p><p> This was in retaliation against Joe Rogan – podcast host and sceptic of the COVID vaccination – who was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/neil-young-wants-his-music-removed-from-spotify-immediately-citing-false-information-about-vaccines-3145688">said to be spreading misinformation about the virus</a> by Stills&#39; former bandmate <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/neil-young">Neil Young</a> .</p><p> The music <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/crosby-stills-nashs-music-returns-to-spotify-3261128">returned to the streaming platform shortly after</a> and, earlier this year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-neil-young-and-stephen-stills-reunite-for-first-time-in-four-years-and-pay-tribute-to-david-crosby-3434936">Stills joined Young onstage for the latter&#39;s first concert in four years</a> .</p><p> In other news, in June <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/eric-clapton-2024-uk-ireland-tour-dates-tickets-3453510">Clapton announced details of a new UK and Ireland tour</a> , that is set to take place in May next year.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/eric-clapton-and-stephen-stills-help-raise-millions-for-controversial-robert-f-kennedy-jr-s-presidential-campaign-3501810">Eric Clapton and Stephen Stills help raise millions for controversial Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s Presidential campaign</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
